{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"kind":"article","metadata":{"role":"article","title":"Content Bundles","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Gnusto"}]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Composing Large Games","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin"],"anchor":"Composing-Large-Games"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","isActive":true},{"text":" shows how a game’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"text":" compose from per-region helpers, but its ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"entity declarations"}]},{"text":" all have to stay in the one ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Game","isActive":true},{"text":" struct’s body. Content bundles lift that limit. A bundle is a self-contained slice of the world — its own rooms, items, and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"text":" state, plus the geography, rules, and verbs that go with them — declared in its own type, and even its own SPM package.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Reach for a bundle when a region is big or independent enough to own its declarations (not just its ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"text":"), or when you want to ship a region as a reusable package. For everything smaller, the extension-based file split is lighter and is still the right tool.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"A bundle is a `GameContent`","anchor":"A-bundle-is-a-GameContent","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct Attic: GameContent {","    let landing = Location { name(\"Attic Landing\"); description(\"A dim landing.\") }","    let trunk   = Item { name(\"steamer trunk\"); adjectives(\"steamer\") }","","    var map: WorldMap { trunk.starts(in: landing) }","","    var rules: Rules {","        trunk.before(.open) { try reply(\"It's locked.\") }","    }","","    var verbs: [SyntaxRule] {        \/\/ optional — bundles can add verbs too","        SyntaxRule(\"rummage\", slots: .direct, intent: Intent(\"rummage\"))","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"text":", and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"verbs"},{"type":"text","text":" all default to empty, so a bundle declares only what it needs. The bundle stores its declarations exactly as a game does, and the bootstrap discovers them by reflecting over the bundle. Each entity is named after its property, prefixed by the bundle’s "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles#EntityIDs-are-namespaced-by-the-bundle","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"namespace","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"namespace","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trunk"},{"type":"text","text":" → "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/EntityID","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Attic.trunk\""},{"type":"text","text":"), so a reusable bundle can’t collide with the host."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"The game lists its bundles in `content`","anchor":"The-game-lists-its-bundles-in-content","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct MyGame: Game {","    let attic  = Attic()","    let cellar = Cellar()","","    var content: GameContents {","        attic","        cellar","    }","","    var map: WorldMap {","        attic.landing.down(cellar.vault)   \/\/ cross-bundle wiring, top level","        player.starts(in: attic.landing)","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The game’s own ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"verbs"},{"text":" still work and are merged with every bundle’s.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"The one rule: list the stored instances","anchor":"The-one-rule-list-the-stored-instances","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"content"},{"type":"text","text":" must yield the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"same bundle instances the game stores"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"var content { attic; cellar }"},{"type":"text","text":", never "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"var content { Attic(); Cellar() }"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global"},{"type":"text","text":" mints a reference token when it’s created, and the bootstrap matches the tokens it discovers against the tokens a bundle’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":" reference. A freshly constructed bundle carries "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"different"}]},{"type":"text","text":" tokens than the one the game stored, so its references wouldn’t resolve. Listing the stored instances keeps the identities aligned. (The bootstrap reads "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"content"},{"type":"text","text":" once and reuses it, so a single build is always self-consistent; the contract matters because the game’s top-level "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"type":"text","text":" references the stored "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"attic"},{"type":"text","text":".)"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"EntityIDs are namespaced by the bundle","anchor":"EntityIDs-are-namespaced-by-the-bundle","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A bundle’s entities are namespaced by the bundle, while the game’s own entities stay bare. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"attic.landing"},{"type":"text","text":" becomes "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/EntityID"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Attic.landing\""},{"type":"text","text":"; the game’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"foyer"},{"type":"text","text":" stays "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"foyer\""},{"type":"text","text":". The namespace defaults to the bundle’s "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"type name"}]},{"type":"text","text":", so each distinct bundle type gets a distinct prefix automatically and a reusable bundle dropped into any host can’t clash — even if the host and the bundle both declare a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"landing"},{"type":"text","text":", they resolve to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"landing\""},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"Attic.landing\""},{"type":"text","text":". References at the authoring site are token-based ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"attic.landing"},{"type":"text","text":"), so the namespace is invisible there; it only shows up in the raw ID string, which is internal (display and parsing use each entity’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"name(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Collisions are still fatal, but now only when two bundles share a namespace "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"and"}]},{"type":"text","text":" a property name. That happens when a host stores "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"two instances of the same bundle type"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — both default to the type-name namespace, so "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Attic.landing"},{"type":"text","text":" is declared twice and the bootstrap rejects the game: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"entity \"Attic.landing\" is declared by both Attic and Attic."},{"type":"text","text":" Give each instance a distinct namespace by overriding "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"var namespace"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct Attic: GameContent {","    let name: String","    var namespace: String { name }   \/\/ \"NorthAttic\", \"SouthAttic\", …","    \/\/ …","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because bundle-owned entity IDs are namespaced, so are their save-file keys — a bundle’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":" persists under "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Bundle.flag"},{"type":"text","text":". Nothing shipped before this change owned bundle content, so there’s no migration; keep a plugin’s own state additive as usual."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Cross-bundle-references","level":2,"text":"Cross-bundle references"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Top-level wiring"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — a game connecting one bundle’s room to another’s — is ordinary, compile-checked property access: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"attic.landing.down(cellar.vault)"},{"type":"text","text":". Renaming either room breaks the exit at compile time."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Bundle-to-bundle"}]},{"type":"text","text":" references (a bundle that needs to point at another bundle’s entity from "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"inside"}]},{"type":"text","text":" its own "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":") use explicit injection: construct the dependency first and hand the shared instance in ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Attic(cellarDoor: cellar.door)"},{"type":"text","text":"), so both sides reference the same token. Keep these localized; most cross-region wiring belongs at the top level."}]}]}]},{"text":"Multi-package","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Multi-package"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because a bundle is a self-contained "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"type":"text","text":" value type, it can live in its own SPM module: export the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent"},{"type":"text","text":" type, depend on it from the host, and list it in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"content"},{"type":"text","text":". Nothing else changes."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Worked-example","level":2,"text":"Worked example"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tests\/GnustoTests\/Support\/BundleGame\/"},{"type":"text","text":" is a minimal game built this way: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AtticContent"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CellarContent"},{"type":"text","text":" each own a room, an item, and rules (the attic also adds a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rummage"},{"type":"text","text":" verb), and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"BundleGame"},{"type":"text","text":" composes them with a cross-bundle exit. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"BundleCompositionTests"},{"type":"text","text":" boots it and confirms every bundle’s rules and verbs fire, the cross-bundle exit traverses both ways, each bundle’s IDs are namespaced by its type, and two instances sharing a namespace are rejected."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For a bundle that also carries logic over the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"host’s","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" world — a content-bearing plugin — see "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Give a region its own declarations — its own type, and even its own package."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gnusto\/contentbundles"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto"]]},"references":{"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Plugins":{"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Plugins","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Package a reusable game system as an importable unit of verbs and rules."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/plugins"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GamePlugin":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"GamePlugin","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GamePlugin"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A reusable game system — commerce, combat, dialog, magic — packaged as an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"importable unit of "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"verbs"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"rules"}]},{"type":"text","text":", that a host game opts into."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gameplugin","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GamePlugin"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Global":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"Global","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Global"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom game state with the same ergonomics as built-in state:"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/global","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Global"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Swift engine for writing parser-driven interactive fiction — text adventures in the tradition of Zork and Infocom’s ZIL."}],"title":"Gnusto"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/ContentBundles#EntityIDs-are-namespaced-by-the-bundle":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles#EntityIDs-are-namespaced-by-the-bundle","title":"EntityIDs are namespaced by the bundle","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/contentbundles#EntityIDs-are-namespaced-by-the-bundle","type":"topic","kind":"section"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Location":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"Location","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Location"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A place in the world."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/location","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Location"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Game":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Game","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"Game","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Game"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A complete game: declarations, geography, and rules."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/game","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Game"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/EntityID":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/EntityID","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"EntityID","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"EntityID"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A stable, human-readable entity name derived from the Swift property label"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at registration time ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"let bar = Location { … }"},{"type":"text","text":" → "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EntityID(\"bar\")"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/entityid","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"EntityID"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GameContents":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"GameContents","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContents"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The collected content bundles a game declares, in declaration order."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gamecontents","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContents"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles":{"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"Splitting a Game Across Files","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Keep a large game readable by composing its map and rules from per-region helpers."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/splittingagameacrossfiles"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Item":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"Item","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Item"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A thing in the world."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/item","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Item"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GameContent":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","title":"GameContent","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContent"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A self-contained slice of a game’s world: its own rooms, items, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":" state, plus the geography, rules, and verbs that go with them."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gamecontent","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContent"}]}}}